******
[3] Apataki atoll
Date: Thu 16 Oct 2014
Source: Polynesie [in French, trans. CopyEd.LMI, edited]
http://polynesie.la1ere.fr/2014/10/16/la-moitie-de-la-population-de-apataki-touchee-par-le-chikungunya-198628.html


Half of the population of Apataki is affected by chikungunya
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Chikungunya has hit the Apataki atoll [French Polynesia] really hard. According to Rosalie Orbeck, mayor of this atoll in the Tuamotus, one case occurs per day. More than half of the population would be affected. Is this the sign of an extensive epidemic that will affect all archipelagos?

The situation on the atoll is worrisome: "Half of the population has been affected really fast. Every day there are people coming in, there are already 30 confirmed laboratory cases, and still new cases keep arriving," said Rosalie Orbeck.

How do you manage? [she was asked.]

The mayor said: "Doctors recommend to take paracetamol and drink plenty of water. It's the only medicine that can ease the pain. The patients who have a high fever (39 or 40 deg C) are in real pain. They sometimes can't even walk. Some stay at home, others can make it to the hospital. They are all lying here unable to stand up," concluded the Mayor.

[Byline: Pierre-Emmanuel Garot]

