[The outbreak of chikungunya fever is spreading rapidly and intensifying in French Polynesia. Tahiti is part of the Society Island archipelago and capital of the collectivity that is French Polynesia. Given the inter-island movement within French Polynesia, it is not surprising to see chikungunya virus appear on Tahiti, the most populous of these islands, as Zika virus did in 2013. Now, there are suspected cases of chikungunya virus infection on Tubuai, Raiatea and Apataki atoll. Since there are no commercially available vaccines available yet for chikungunya virus, the only preventive measures are vector control and avoidance of mosquito bites.

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail showing the location of Tahiti in French Polynesia can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2875482,22997. The Apataki atoll is one of the Palliser Islands, a subgroup of the Tuamotu Archipelago. A map showing its location can be accessed at http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apataki#mediaviewer/File:Tuamotus_Locator_Apataki.jpg. - Mod.TY]
